s Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"Geoff\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1480:\"<p>Events Calendar PRO 3.12.6 is fresh off the presses and available at this very moment. This is a teeny-tiny update but resolves a significant issue with PRO&#8217;s widgets:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fix:</strong> Ensure the correct date displays within the upcoming events list widget</li>\n</ul>\n<p>In short, there were instances where the date in the widget&#8217;s icon for an event was displaying the previous day&#8217;s number instead of the current day. Our thanks to Seth, @farmgirlref and others for highlighting this in the forums and helping us track down the cause of it.</p>\n<p>We expect no issues if you&#8217;re updating from Events Calendar PRO 3.12 or greater. As always, be mindful when updating from version 3.11 or lower. We suggest reading through the <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/category/products/release-notes/\">release notes</a> before updating from earlier versions and testing in a development environment with backups as you would any other WordPress update.</p>\n<p>Thanks and please do feel free to <a href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/support/forums/forum/events/events-calendar-pro/\">hit us up in the forums</a> if you experience any issues after updating and we&#8217;d be happy to help!</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com/release-events-calendar-pro-3-12-6/\">Release: Events Calendar PRO 3.12.6</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://theeventscalendar.com\">The Events Calendar</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\"